        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Numerical solver error acceptance criteria — Gradation 3",
        "description": "Iterative convergence must be demonstrated via residual monitoring and QoI monitor stabilisation. Residuals must reach at minimum 10⁻⁴; QoI change over final 10% of iterations must be less than 0.5%. Double-precision arithmetic must be used. Solver configuration must be documented and archived."
      }
    },
    {
