      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "RANS k-ω SST turbulence model selected based on literature benchmark performance for confined rotating flows (Hariharan et al. 2011, Stewart et al. 2012). Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al. 1990) with modified coefficients (Zhang et al. 2011) used. Model form uncertainty estimated via comparison of three turbulence model variants (k-ε realizable, k-ω SST, Spalart-Allmaras); NIH spread across models 6.2%, within UQ envelope. Model form selection rationale documented in MFR-2025-001.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
