        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Model form acceptance criteria — Gradation 3",
        "description": "Turbulence and hemolysis model selection must be justified by reference to published benchmarks for geometrically similar flows. Model form uncertainty must be estimated by comparison of at least two alternative model forms. Model form spread must be within the reported UQ prediction interval. Selection rationale must be documented."
      }
    },
    {
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
